International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: Tue 16 Jul 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ontario Ministry of Health and Long Term Care, West Nile Virus
Bulletin,
Tue 12 Jul 2002 [edited]
<http://www.gov.on.ca/health/english/program/pubhealth/wnv_mn.html>

Windsor-Essex Bird is 10th West Nile virus-positive Bird in in Ontario
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Health and Long-Term Care works with local public health units
and Health Canada to monitor the presence of West Nile virus (WNV) in the
province.
As of Tue 12 Jul 2002, 10 birds have been confirmed positive for WNV in
Ontario,
as follows (species not given):
Peel Region, 1 confirmed (collected 19 May 2002);
Oxford Region, 1 confirmed (collected 4 Jun 2002);
Chatham-Kent Region, 5 confirmed (collected 12 to 14 Jun 2002);
Middlesex-London Region, 1 confirmed (collected 17 Jun 2002);
Halton Region, 1 confirmed (collected 15 Jun 2002).
Windsor-Essex, 1 confirmed (collected 18 Jun 2002)
The presence of West Nile virus in Canada was confirmed first on 22 Aug
2001 in a
bird submitted from Windsor-Essex Country. Neither the virus nor its symptoms
have been detected in humans to date.
******
[2]
Date: Tue 16 Jul 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Perth District Health Unit, news release, 12 Jul 2002 [edited]
<http://www.pdhu.on.ca/news/07_12_02.htm>

Perth County Crow Positive for West Nile Virus
----------------------------------------------
STRATFORD: Initial tests on a dead crow found in Stratford on 8 Jul 2002 have
come back positive for West Nile virus. This is the first bird in Perth
County to
show West Nile virus infection and the 11th in the province this year.
Positive
birds have also been found recently in London, Woodstock, Chatham, Windsor,
and
Mississauga.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[As of Tue 12 Jul 2002, 11 birds have been confirmed positive for West Nile
virus
in Ontario. The number of West Nile virus-positive birds confirmed in
Ontario has
increased by 2 since Wed 3 Jul 2002. - Mod.CP]
